Dear employees. Due to the abuse of the Internet during working hours, we have disabled
access to it on all office computers indefinitely. Treat this with understanding, it is 
important for us to see you happy and rested, but it is also equally important to fulfill
the work plan. Don't forget what a serious project you are working on.
Sincerely, the administration of the third sector of Giero Labs.

Dear employees. Due to the abuse of the Internet during working hours, we have disabled

the work plan. Don't forget what a serious project you are working on.

column1:
From Jiofef to everyone.
For more than a year of development, I have not used almost any other people's assets.
However, I couldn't create some things myself in the form I wanted, so I had to borrow.
I want to thank:
FFF Media Inc and Daymarius for the fonts.
sfxBUZZ and SoundJay for some sounds.
Pixabay for various assets, mostly sounds.
The developers of Katana ZERO for the sound of laughter.

Everything else was done by the only employee of the Paradise Underground studio under
the nickname Jiofef



All rights reserved btw ;p

From Jiofef to everyone.
For more than a year of development, I have not used almost any other people's assets.
However, I couldn't create some things myself in the form I wanted, so I had to borrow.

column1:
To the Board of Directors of Giero.
I am glad to inform you that the testing and training of object 24 "Slippey" (hereinafter
referred to as the "object") was successful. The object is subject to further cloning and
the use of clones for military purposes in accordance with Order N43 of 03/27/2039.
Our laboratories will conduct additional testing and begin the cloning operation in the
near future.
With respect,
The general manager of Giero Labs, Hiro Miyoshi.
en:
To the Board of Directors of Giero.
I am glad to inform you that the testing and training of object 24 "Slippey" (hereinafter
referred to as the "object") was successful. The object is subject to further cloning and
the use of clones for military purposes in accordance with Order N43 of 03/27/2039.
Our laboratories will conduct additional testing and begin the cloning operation in the
near future.
With respect,
The general manager of Giero Labs, Hiro Miyoshi.
